class UserStory:
    def __init__(self, user_type, description):
        self.user_type = user_type
        self.description = description

class Cluster:
    def __init__(self, cluster_id):
        self.cluster_id = cluster_id
        self.user_stories = []

    def add_user_story(self, user_story):
        self.user_stories.append(user_story)

class System:
    def __init__(self):
        self.clusters = {}

    def add_cluster(self, cluster):
        self.clusters[cluster.cluster_id] = cluster

    def process_user_stories(self):
        for cluster in self.clusters.values():
            print(f"Processing Cluster {cluster.cluster_id}:")
            for story in cluster.user_stories:
                self.handle_user_story(story)

    def handle_user_story(self, story):
        print(f" - {story.user_type}: {story.description}")

# Initializing the system
system = System()

# Clusters and user stories
